  "title": "Hinduism and Other Religions of India",
  "outline": [
    {
      "level": "A",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "History of Hinduism",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The origins of Hinduism: Indo-European roots and other influences",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The prehistoric and protohistoric periods, through the 2nd millennium bc: the religions of the indigenous prehistoric peoples and of the Indus Valley civilization",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "3",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The Vedic period (2nd millennium-7th century bc) , a. The religion of the Rgveda",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "The religion of the later Vedas and Brahmanas",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "The religion of the Upanisads",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": "4",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The heterodox period (7th-2nd century bc): challenges to Brahmanism by reformers and ascetic groups [see also D.I., below, and 824]",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "5",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The early Hindu period (2nd century BC-4th century ad): the rise of the major sects and other developments",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "6",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The Puranic period (4th-8th century)",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "7",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The rise of devotional Hinduism (8th- 11th century): the Tamil hymnists, the Bhagavata-Purana after Hinduism",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "8",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The age of bhakti (1 1th- 19th century)",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "9",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The modem period (19th-20th century)",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "10",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Hinduism today",
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
